                            <comment id="86498" author="haasken" created="Thu, 12 Jun 2014 23:33:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is a potential patch:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/10707/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/10707/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The lustre_manual.html that I built with this patch no longer has the version labels overlapping the text.  If somebody has a better way to achieve this, please feel free to correct me since I don&apos;t have any experience with CSS and XSL.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="86492" author="haasken" created="Thu, 12 Jun 2014 23:12:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue pertains to the html version of the documentation.&lt;/p&gt;

